snippet.textDisplay: I hate how she knows how good she is and she's trying to hide it. That's not sincere and it shows in the way she composes herself. She can sing but her quality indicates that she has experience with her voice. In other words the panel of judges has little to coach her on which means she just wants recognition. Her pitch, tonality, and diction are there but she is off tempo and her breathing is not in tandem with her vocal coordination. I hope she is open to learning because if she thinks talent gets her a pass she should reconsider her career options.
